Patch Set 8:

What exactly will setting delay_auth_decision to True change in terms of authenticating registry requests?

(Registry responses can contain sensitive information.)

Patch Set 8:

This is for solving the bug.
https://bugs.launchpad.net/glance/+bug/1470164

When glance-api enable allow_anonymous
glance-api failed to get information from glance-registry if the rquest is anonymous because glance-registry doesn't find auth token.

We need to prevent from that teh "authtoken" raise "token not found" exception too earily.

the way is the same as glance-api-paste.ini.
https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/etc/glance-api-paste.ini#L76

Patch Set 8:

Do we really need to do this via overrides in paste ? By over-riding this in paste settings, the delay_auth_decision in glance conf's keystone_authtoken section will have no effect. Can't we ask user to set this to True alongside allow_anonymous_access = True in the conf files ?

Patch Set 8:

setting "allow_anonymous_access = True" in glance-registry is not enough because "authtoken" raise exception too early.

If we don't add "delay_auth_decision = true", glance-registry will raise the exception, "token not found", even if we set "allow_anonymous_access = True" in glance-registry.conf.

Patch Set 8:

＠Sabari
Do you means there are the optinon, "delay_auth_decision", in glance-registry.conf ?

Patch Set 8:

Yes, check the keystone_authtoken section in both confs.

Patch Set 8:
